# Vuetify Rules

## Component Naming

- Use kebab-case for Vuetify components: `v-card`, `v-btn`, `v-container`
- All Vuetify components start with `v-` prefix
- Component names are lowercase with hyphens

## Common Vuetify Components

- **Layout**: `v-app`, `v-main`, `v-container`, `v-row`, `v-col`
- **Cards**: `v-card`, `v-card-title`, `v-card-text`, `v-card-actions`
- **Buttons**: `v-btn` with props like `color`, `size`, `icon`, `text`, `outlined`
- **Navigation**: `v-tabs`, `v-tab`, `v-app-bar`, `v-toolbar-title`
- **Forms**: `v-text-field`, `v-select`, `v-file-input`, `v-checkbox`
- **Feedback**: `v-alert`, `v-dialog`, `v-snackbar`, `v-progress-circular`
- **Data Display**: `v-table`, `v-data-table`, `v-list`, `v-list-item`

## Vuetify Directives

- Use Vuetify utility classes: `d-flex`, `flex-column`, `justify-center`, `align-center`
- Spacing classes: `mt-4`, `mb-2`, `pa-4`, `ma-2` (margin/padding)
- Text classes: `text-h5`, `text-caption`, `text--secondary`
- Color classes: `color="primary"`, `color="success"`, `color="error"`

## Component Props

- **v-btn**: `color`, `size`, `icon`, `text`, `outlined`, `disabled`, `loading`
- **v-card**: `elevation`, `outlined`, `flat`
- **v-dialog**: `:value="boolean"`, `@input="handler"`, `max-width`
- **v-file-input**: `:label`, `:accept`, `@change`
- **v-alert**: `type` (error, warning, info, success), `prominent`, `dismissible`
- **v-progress-circular**: `indeterminate`, `color`

## Event Handling

- Use `@click` for button clicks
- Use `@input` for dialog close events: `@input="onClose"`
- Use `@change` for file inputs and form changes
- Bind dialog visibility: `:value="isOpen"` with `@input="isOpen = $event"`

## Theming

- Vuetify theme is configured in the main app file
- Use theme colors: `primary`, `secondary`, `accent`, `error`, `info`, `success`, `warning`
- Apply colors via props: `color="primary"` or classes

## Common Patterns

### Dialog/Modal Pattern
```javascript
<v-dialog
  :value="isOpen"
  @input="onClose"
  max-width="600"
>
  <v-card>
    <v-card-title>Title</v-card-title>
    <v-card-text>Content</v-card-text>
    <v-card-actions>
      <v-spacer></v-spacer>
      <v-btn text @click="onClose">Cancel</v-btn>
    </v-card-actions>
  </v-card>
</v-dialog>
```

### Button with Icon
```javascript
<v-btn color="primary" @click="handleClick">
  <v-icon left>mdi-icon-name</v-icon>
  Button Text
</v-btn>
```

### Alert with Actions
```javascript
<v-alert type="error" prominent>
  <div class="font-weight-bold mb-2">Error Title</div>
  <div>{{ errorMessage }}</div>
  <v-btn color="primary" @click="handleAction">Action</v-btn>
</v-alert>
```

### Tabs
```javascript
<v-tabs :value="activeTab" @change="handleTabChange">
  <v-tab v-for="tab in tabs" :key="tab" :value="tab">
    {{ tabName }}
  </v-tab>
</v-tabs>
```

## Icons

- Use Material Design Icons with `mdi-` prefix
- Icon component: `<v-icon>mdi-icon-name</v-icon>`
- Icon in button: `<v-icon left>mdi-icon-name</v-icon>`
- Common icons: `mdi-arrow-left`, `mdi-file-document`, `mdi-database`, `mdi-close`

## Layout Structure

- Wrap app in `<v-app>` at root level
- Use `<v-main>` for main content area
- Use `<v-container>` for content padding and max-width
- Use `<v-row>` and `<v-col>` for grid layouts (if needed)

## Best Practices

- Always close Vuetify components properly
- Use Vuetify spacing utilities instead of custom CSS when possible
- Leverage Vuetify's built-in responsive design classes
- Use semantic Vuetify components over custom HTML when available
- Follow Vuetify's accessibility guidelines
